# **10-Day ML Training — Recommended Sources**

### **Day 1 — Python & Jupyter Basics**

* **Concepts**: Python syntax, loops, functions, lists/dicts, basic pandas & numpy
* **Read/Watch**:

  * [W3Schools Python Tutorial](https://www.w3schools.com/python/)
  * [Automate the Boring Stuff with Python](https://automatetheboringstuff.com/) (free online book)
  * [Python for Data Science — freeCodeCamp YouTube](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LHBE6Q9XlzI)
* **Practice**: Titanic CSV, simple filtering, basic stats

---

### **Day 2 — Linear Regression**

* **Concepts**: Predict numeric targets, understand slope/intercept, RMSE
* **Read/Watch**:

  * [Scikit-learn Linear Regression](https://scikit-learn.org/stable/modules/linear_model.html#linear-regression)
  * [Linear Regression in Python (YouTube)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=J_LnPL3Qg70)
* **Dataset**: Boston Housing dataset (built-in `sklearn.datasets`)

---

### **Day 3 — Logistic Regression**

* **Concepts**: Binary classification, probability outputs, confusion matrix
* **Read/Watch**:

  * [Scikit-learn Logistic Regression](https://scikit-learn.org/stable/modules/linear_model.html#logistic-regression)
  * [Logistic Regression in Python (YouTube)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yIYKR4sgzI8)
* **Dataset**: Titanic survival prediction, Heart disease dataset

---

### **Day 4 — Decision Tree**

* **Concepts**: Tree structure, splitting, overfitting, feature importance
* **Read/Watch**:

  * [Decision Trees — scikit-learn](https://scikit-learn.org/stable/modules/tree.html)
  * [Decision Trees Explained (YouTube)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7VeUPuFGJHk)
* **Dataset**: Iris dataset

---

### **Day 5 — Random Forest**

* **Concepts**: Ensemble learning, bagging, improved accuracy, feature importance
* **Read/Watch**:

  * [Random Forest — scikit-learn](https://scikit-learn.org/stable/modules/ensemble.html#random-forests)
  * [Random Forests Tutorial (YouTube)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=J4Wdy0Wc_xQ)
* **Dataset**: Breast Cancer dataset (built-in `sklearn.datasets`)

---

### **Day 6 — K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN)**

* **Concepts**: Similarity-based classification/regression, distance metrics
* **Read/Watch**:

  * [KNN — scikit-learn](https://scikit-learn.org/stable/modules/neighbors.html)
  * [KNN Algorithm Python Tutorial (YouTube)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HVXime0nQeI)
* **Dataset**: Small MNIST sample or Iris dataset

---

### **Day 7 — Support Vector Machine (SVM)**

* **Concepts**: Hyperplanes, kernels, margin maximization
* **Read/Watch**:

  * [SVM — scikit-learn](https://scikit-learn.org/stable/modules/svm.html)
  * [SVM Intuition (YouTube)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=efR1C6CvhmE)
* **Dataset**: Iris dataset

---

### **Day 8 — K-Means Clustering**

* **Concepts**: Unsupervised learning, clustering, centroids, inertia
* **Read/Watch**:

  * [K-Means — scikit-learn](https://scikit-learn.org/stable/modules/clustering.html#k-means)
  * [K-Means Clustering in Python (YouTube)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4b5d3muPQmA)
* **Dataset**: Customer segmentation or synthetic dataset (`make_blobs` from sklearn)

---

### **Day 9 — PCA (Dimensionality Reduction)**

* **Concepts**: Reduce features, visualize high-dimensional data, variance explained
* **Read/Watch**:

  * [PCA — scikit-learn](https://scikit-learn.org/stable/modules/decomposition.html#pca)
  * [PCA Explained (YouTube)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FgakZw6K1QQ)
* **Dataset**: Wine dataset (built-in `sklearn.datasets`)

---

### **Day 10 — Neural Networks Intro**

* **Concepts**: MLP (Multi-Layer Perceptron), forward/backward pass, activation functions
* **Read/Watch**:

  * [MLP — scikit-learn](https://scikit-learn.org/stable/modules/neural_networks_supervised.html)
  * [Simple Neural Network Python Tutorial (YouTube)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aircAruvnKk)
  * Optional: TensorFlow/Keras intro [TensorFlow tutorials](https://www.tensorflow.org/tutorials)
* **Dataset**: MNIST digits (small subset)

---

### **Additional Resources**

* **Kaggle for practice datasets**: [https://www.kaggle.com/datasets](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets)
* **Hands-on ML book (optional, highly recommended)**: *Hands-On Machine Learning with Scikit-Learn, Keras & TensorFlow* by Aurélien Géron
* **Jupyter + Git workflow**: [GitHub Docs — Git Basics](https://docs.github.com/en/get-started/quickstart)

---
